INSERT INTO `helps` VALUES (1,'GREETING','.     ######## ##     ## ########       ######  ########  #### ##     ##  ######   #######  ##    ## \n        ##    ##     ## ##            ##    ## ##     ##  ##  ###   ### ##    ## ##     ## ###   ## \n        ##    ##     ## ##            ##       ##     ##  ##  #### #### ##       ##     ## ####  ## \n        ##    ######### ######        ##       ########   ##  ## ### ##  ######  ##     ## ## ## ## \n        ##    ##     ## ##            ##       ##   ##    ##  ##     ##       ## ##     ## ##  #### \n        ##    ##     ## ##            ##    ## ##    ##   ##  ##     ## ##    ## ##     ## ##   ### \n        ##    ##     ## ########       ######  ##     ## #### ##     ##  ######   #######  ##    ## \n \n ######  ########    ###    #### ##    ## ######## ########     ##          ###    ##    ## ########   ######  \n##    ##    ##      ## ##    ##  ###   ## ##       ##     ##    ##         ## ##   ###   ## ##     ## ##    ## \n##          ##     ##   ##   ##  ####  ## ##       ##     ##    ##        ##   ##  ####  ## ##     ## ##       \n ######     ##    ##     ##  ##  ## ## ## ######   ##     ##    ##       ##     ## ## ## ## ##     ##  ######  \n      ##    ##    #########  ##  ##  #### ##       ##     ##    ##       ######### ##  #### ##     ##       ## \n##    ##    ##    ##     ##  ##  ##   ### ##       ##     ##    ##       ##     ## ##   ### ##     ## ##    ## \n ######     ##    ##     ## #### ##    ## ######## ########     ######## ##     ## ##    ## ########   ######  \n \nA shimmering myriad of blazing white lines flashes across your plane of vision.\n- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -\\x\nYour body stretches and warps violently beneath your spirit as it struggles to become alive once again. \n\\g@ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @ @\\x\nSomewhere in the depths of your memories, faded and blurred, a quiet voice pleads with you, \'Do not forget...\'\n\nAs quickly as the voice entered your mind, it drifts away.\n\nAll you know is that you are now within the King\'s Labyrinth...',-1,'2023-08-07 14:19:42',''),(6,'DIKU','.                    Original game idea, concept, and design:\n\n          Katja Nyboe               [Superwoman] (katz@freja.diku.dk)\n          Tom Madsen              [Stormbringer] (noop@freja.diku.dk)\n          Hans Henrik Staerfeldt           [God] (bombman@freja.diku.dk)\n          Michael Seifert                 [Papi] (seifert@freja.diku.dk)\n          Sebastian Hammer               [Quinn] (quinn@freja.diku.dk)\n\n\nDeveloped at: DIKU -- The Department of Computer Science\n                      at the University of Copenhagen.\n\nThis mud is also based on Merc 2.1, created by Furey, Hatchet, and Kahn.\nSee help \'MERC\' for more information.\n\nROM 2.4 beta, copyright 1993 - 1996 Russ Taylor\nROM was started in early February 1993, using Merc 1.0 code.\nSee help \'ROM\' for more information\n\nThe Tartarus Code enhancedments and additions \nare copyright (C) 1997, 1998 by Daniel Graham\nSee help \'TARTARUS\' for more information',-1,'2023-08-07 14:19:42',''),(11,'ROM','ROM started in early February 1993, using Merc 1.0 code. In July of 1993,  \nROM II was started, eventually replacing the original ROM.  ROM was up for\na little over a year, after which the code (version 2.3) was released,\nand various other ROM muds were started, including Rivers of Mud under\na new management (Zump\'s ROM), at rom.org 9000.\n\nAlander\'s current project is Athen, the sequel to the ROM code.\nIt will be found at hypercube.org 6666, when it is opened.\n\nThe following people contributed to the ROM flavor of the merc base code:\n\nSocials --\n    Kelsey and Liralen\n\nNew, Improved Valhalla --\n    Liralen\n\nPuff\'s new special proc and improved poofin/poofout code --\n    Seth\n\nMaps and map shop --\n    Ezra, Regnan (Olympus)\n\nNirvana zone --\n    Forstall (mobiles rewritten by Alander)\n\nMob Factory --\n    Pinkfloyd (originally written for ROM, mobiles rewritten by Alander)\n\nGeographically correct Midgaard (tm) --\n    Alander\n\nIdeas and playtesting --\n    Thousands of dedicated mudders around the world\n\nBeta testing --\n    Ken Blosser, Doug Araya, and Sherene Neil all helped with bug reports\n    and suggestions, saving a lot of headaches\n\nNew Thalos area was donated by Onivel of Jedi, who was also the originator\nof the ASCII flags used in the zone files\nROM 2.4 was developed during my time with Moosehead mud, and the\nrelease\nshares many of the features I wrote while I was there.  Additional code\nwas written by Seth Scott (enchant armor, the new poofin/poofout), and many\ncontributions and ideas from the Merc list were used.  Portions of Rusty\'s\ncode from Moosehead also remain.\n\nThe new features of 2.4 were largely produced in bull sessions with\nGabrielle Taylor and Brian Moore, without whom this release wouldn\'t\nhave happened.  In particular, the new privacy code, furniture, and\nwiznet are largely the results of Gabrielle\'s ideas.\n\nChanges to the standard diku mob and object format, as well as the changes\nto Merc 2.1 source code, were done by Alander over many a late night of\nhair-pulling. Hope you enjoy it.\n\n(my apologies if anyone was forgotten in this list)',-1,'2023-08-07 14:19:42',''),(16,'MERC','This mud is based on Merc 2.1, created by Furey, Hatchet, and Kahn.  \nMerc 2.1 is available as Merc_21.tar.gz from ftp.tcp.com and \nftp.math.okstate.edu.\nE-mail to \'majordomo@webnexus.com\' to join the merc mailing list.\n\nThanks to ...\n  ... Diku Mud for starting it all.\n  ... The Free Software Foundation and DJ Delorie for kick-ass tools.\n  ... Copper Mud and Alfa Mud for releasing their code and worlds.\n  ... Aod of Generic for ... well, everything.  You\'re a hoopy frood, Aod.\n  ... Alander for many ideas and contributions.\n  ... John Brothers of Silly for permission to use Silly code and worlds.\n  ... Zrin for administering the mailing list.\n  ... Abaddon for proofreading our comm.c.\n  ... Hind, Quin, Vic, Diavolo, Oleg, Trienne, and others for porting help.\n  ... Diavolo, Grodyn, Morgenes, and others for code and bug fixes.\n  ... Raff, Doctor, VampLestat, Nirrad, Tyrst, PinkF, Chris, Glop for worlds.\n  ... the players and imps of Mud Dome, Final Mud, Mud Lite, Vego Mud, Rivers\n      of Mud, Ruhr Mud, and Mystic Realms for bug reports, ideas, new code,\n      and hours of enjoyment.\n\nAlso see \"help ROM\" for information about the Rivers of Mud code base.',-1,'2023-08-07 14:19:42',''),(21,'TARTARUS','Tartarus code was started in late 1996 and completed around mid 1997. It\nwas developed at darkmists.mudservices.com for use on the mud Dark Mists\nand used Rom2.4b3 code. The original coder on the mud was Thrym who\nbegan the mud with Styx, who contributed ideas and help. Ceran joined\nthe team and contributed most of the core code, including all the class\nand clan skills/spells as well as the majority of fully new code, before\nleaving in 1997 because of conflicts with the other immortals.\n\nThis code release is named Tartarus and contains Ceran\'s original coding\nplus rewritten code. This code is for use on Rom2.4b muds, although it can\nbe easily hacked for parts to use on other code bases. It is provided\nsolely for the MUDing community as a way of giving back to it what has\nbeen freely given many times before.\nThe following people contributed to the Tartarus release:\n\nCode --\n	Thrym who installed the MOBProgs patch into the base ROM code.\n\nAreas --\n	-Lilith (Arkham) (Unable to contact this person. See \n         README.tararus file which comes with this derivative code)\n	-Kay, who wrote a lot of Nightfall and Thorbardin.\n	-Zenan, who did Rakshasa Domain when I got bogged down with code\n         and other areas.',-1,'2023-08-07 14:19:42',''),(1100000,'peek','When looking at someone, a thief attempts to peek at their inventory.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100005,'\'enhanced damage\'','Chance per hit to increase damage.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100010,'\'enhanced damage ii\'','When enhanced damage chance succeeds, gain another chance per hit to increase damage further.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100015,'spellcraft','Chance per spell cast to increase damage.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100020,'\'spellcraft ii\'','Increases spellcrafts chance to be successful.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100025,'\'fast healing\'','Chance to increase rate of healing in all positions.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100030,'meditation','Chance to increase rate of mana gained in all positions.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100035,'trance','Chance to increase rate of mana gained in all positions.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100040,'\'rogues awareness\'','Chance to know which direction you flee in.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100045,'\'gentle walk\'','Chance that an aggressive npc will ignore your entrance.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100050,'flourintine','Increases chance to parry while dual wielding swords.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100055,'distance','Chance to keep your enemy from hitting you while using a polearm.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100060,'\'defensive spin\'','Increases chance to avoid damage while wielding a staff or spear.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100065,'riposte','You gain a chance to return some damage for eacy parry while wielding a sword.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100070,'survivalist','Reduces the need for food and water.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100075,'\'quiet movement\'','Prevents others from seeing which direction you left in or came from.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100080,'\'path finding\'','Chance to reduce movement points spent while moving within wilderness,\nthis effect is spread to the entire party when leader has this skill.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100085,'\'minor regeneration\'','Chance to heal a small amount between each pulse (250ms).',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100090,'\'major regeration\'','Chance to heal a medium amount between each pulse (250ms).',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100095,'\'greater regeration\'','Chance to heal a moderate amount between each pulse (250ms).',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100100,'\'super regeration\'','Chance to heal a generous amount between each pulse (250ms).',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100105,'\'combat steal\'','Stealing can now be successful while in combat with the victim.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100110,'\'prey on the weak\'','Thieves have learned to take advantage of weak opponents.  As their victim gets \ncloser to death, they push their advantage striking harder blows.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100115,'\'acrobatics\'','Thieves that have become agile and fast because of their pickpocket habits \nlearn to avoid certain blows from other, more warrior-like opponents.  Thieves \nwith this skill have been known to avoid bashes, trips, throws, and \nsurprising attacks such as ambush, charge, etc.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100120,'\'enliven\'','Shapeshifters can enliven certain spells while in form without costing mana. For example,\nif the spell \"fly\" expires while in form, when out of combat a shapeshifter can\n\"enliven fly\" to \"recast\" the spell while in form.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100125,'\'recover of the snake\'','A greater enliven for focus major utility, increases health regeneration while\nin form, equivalent major regeneration.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100130,'\'tiger frenzy\'','A greater enliven for focus major offensive, increases strength and dexterity\nwhile in form.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100135,'\'bestial fury\'','A greater enliven for focus major offensive, increases all damage while in form\nby 25%.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100140,'\'primal tenacity\'','A greater enliven for focus major defensive, increases SavingBreath,\nSavingPetrification, SavingRod, and SavingSpells. Additional resistance\nto mental and negative attacks.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100145,'\'skin of the displacer\'','A greater enliven for focus major defensive, which gives a small chance to\nevade any type of damage, magical or physical.',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100155,'help','Type \'help [keyword]\' to get help on a specific keyword.\nType `help list` to get a list of all the help entries.\nSome topics you could get help on is communication, combat, skills, and\ntraining.',0,'2023-08-07 14:30:40','Giaken'),(1100165,'communication','Type \'newbie [text]\' to ask or answer questions on the newbie channel.\nType \'say [text]\' to speak to the current room.\nType \'whisper [text]\' to speak to the current room without unhiding.\nType \'tell [playername] [text]\' to talk to an individual player.\nType \'yell [text]\' to yell a message to the current area.\nType \'pray [text]\' to send a message to the gods.',0,'2023-08-07 14:31:11','Giaken'),(1100175,'combat','Type \'consider [name]\' to see how an NPC\'s level compares to your own.\nType \'kill [name]\' to initiate combat with a creature.\nSome NPCs are aggressive and will attack you when you walk in.\nType the name of a skill to perform it in combat if applicable, for example\n\'kick\' while already fighting to perform your kick move.\nMages can \'cast [spellname] [target]\' to use their spells.\nBards can \'sing [song name]\' to sing their songs during combat.',0,'2023-08-07 14:33:08','Giaken'),(1100185,'MOTD','New \'bug\' command to report bugs to the gods.\nNew \'map\' command to draw an ascii map of the surrounding area.\nTyping \'help\' now has a default help entry.\n\'Toggle\' command to change flags such as Auto Loot, or Color\nCheck out the website https://kbs-cloud.com for a map and more\nduelchallenge - Issue a duel challenge to another player.\nduelaccept - Accept a duel challenge from another player.\nduelcancel - Decline a duel challenge from another player.\nAFK flag added. No longer get hungry or thirsty\nafter being inactive for five minutes.\nTyping `help list` will list all help entries\nMap now displays trainers, shops and healers.\nNew replay command to replay the last 20 communications',0,'2023-08-07 14:36:11','Giaken'),(1100195,'skills spells songs supplications','You can type \'practice\' to see a list of all skills, spells and songs you\ncan currently use. Type \'practice [skill/spell/song]\' at a guildmaster to\nlearn an ability better.\nYou can type \'skills\', \'spells\', \'songs\' or \'supplications\' to see a list\nof all the abilities you will ever learn.\nMages use \'cast [ability]\' to cast spells. Priestly guilds\nuse \'commune [ability]\' to use their prayers. Bards use \'sing [ability]\' to\nsing their repertoire of songs.',0,'2023-08-07 14:44:03','Giaken'),(1100205,'train gain training stats','You can train at a trainer or in some cases, at your guildmaster.\nYou start with base stats for your race. These are strength,\nintelligence, wisdom, dexterity, constitution and charisma.\nThese stats affect multiple aspects such as how much(weight/count) you\ncan carry, how much you learn when practicing and how many hitpoints\nyou will gain when you level.\nType \'train\' at a trainer to get a list of what is available to you to train.\nEach race has maximum values a stat can be raised to.\nYou can type \'gain convert\' to convert 10 practices into a train.\nYou can type \'gain revert\' to revert a train into 10 practices.\nYou start with 3 trains and gain 1 train every 5 levels.',0,'2023-08-07 14:47:53','Giaken'),(1100215,'races human elf dwarf orc minotaur','Elf      - starting stats  - 16 str 19 wis 23 int 19 dex 16 con 18 chr\n         - max stats       - 17 str 20 wis 25 int 22 dex 16 con 18 chr\n          (classes) warrior, paladin, healer, mage, shapeshifter, \n           thief, bard, ranger, assassin)\n\nhuman    - starting stats  - 18 str 18 wis 18 int 18 dex 18 con 18 chr\n         - max stats       - 20 str 20 wis 20 int 20 dex 20 con 20 chr\n          (classes) warrior, paladin, healer, mage, shapeshifter, \n           thief, bard, ranger, assassin)\n\ndwarf    - starting stats  - 20 str 18 wis 18 int 16 dex 24 con 15 chr\n         - max stats       - 22 str 18 wis 18 int 17 dex 25 con 16 chr\n          (classes) warrior, paladin, healer, bard, ranger, assassin)\n\norc      - starting stats  -  21 str 15 wis 16 int 19 dex 21 con  8 chr\n         - max stats       - 23 str 17 wis 17 int 20 dex 23 con 12 chr\n          (classes) warrior, healer, thief, bard, ranger, assassin)\n\nminotaur - starting stats  - 21 str 16 wis 17 int 16 dex 20 con 12 chr\n         - max stats       - 23 str 18 wis 18 int 18 dex 22 con 12 chr\n          (classes) none',0,'2023-08-19 19:22:39','Giaken'),(1100225,'classes guilds warrior paladin thief bard mage shapeshifter ranger healer assassin','warrior - focus on weapon specialization, decent at taking and \ndealing damage. Gets a weapon specialization at level 20 and 40.\nMust be proficient in use of a weapon to specialize in it.\nCan shield block, dodge, parry and feint blows.\n\nassassin - focus on martial arts, gets improved kicks upon mastering\nearlier ones. Can dodge and parry. Can bind wounds when injured.\n\nmage - focus on perfecting elements. Unlock new elemental spells as\nyou master earlier spells.\n\nshapeshifter - focus on changing into the forms of animals. First\nform at level 5 - 8, must have a shapefocus major chosen.\n\nthief - great at subterfuge, does better as a sidekick someone else\nstanding in the fore. Can knock enemies out and bind their hands and\nlegs. Can hide and sneak past some enemies and pick locks to open doors\nand containers.\n\nhealer - great at cleansing maladies and restoring the health of their\nfriends. Can grant flight, sanctuary, blessings and a battle frenzy.\n\npaladin - known for taking lead and standing in the fore of combat. They\ncan grant themselves sanctuary. Choose whether to do more damage using\na two handed weapon or block damage with a one handed weapon and a shield.\n\nbard - boost the morale and health of your party, dash the spirits of your\nfoes and cause them harm with offensive lyrics.\n\nranger - excel in the forests, caves, mountains and deserts of the world.\nFind and gather herbs for yourself or your party members to heal wounds.\nTake cover hiding yourself and ambush your prey in the wild. Explore the\nwilds, getting less tired as you move through them. Can fashion their own\nweapons in the wild and eventually be able to imbue them, causing them to\nheal during combat.',0,'2023-08-19 19:42:36','Giaken'),(1100235,'alignment good neutral evil','Good: Characters who are aligned with \"good\" believe in altruism, respect\nfor life, and a desire to help others. They tend to make choices that\nbenefit not just themselves but also those around them, often at their own\nexpense. Good characters are compassionate and will often go out of their\nway to prevent harm to innocents. They uphold values of kindness, charity,\nand self-sacrifice. \n\nNeutral: Neutral characters tend to be more pragmatic\nand do not feel a strong pull towards either extreme of good or evil. Their\nactions may be driven by personal gain, a sense of balance, or the specific\nsituation at hand rather than an inherent moral code. Neutral characters\nmight believe in a natural balance and might act to restore that balance if\nthey feel it\'s been disrupted. They may also prioritize their own\nwell-being or the well-being of their close companions over broader ethical\nor moral considerations. \n\nEvil: Characters who are \"evil\" prioritize their\nown needs and desires over those of others and may be willing to harm or\nmanipulate others to achieve their goals. They might be driven by greed,\npower, anger, hatred, or a desire for revenge. Evil characters might not\nnecessarily be cruel or violent, but they tend to lack empathy for others,\nespecially if there\'s a conflict between their interests and the well-being\nof others. It\'s worth noting that these alignments serve as broad\ncategories, and within them, there can be a lot of variation. For example,\none \"good\" character might be driven by a strong sense of justice, while\nanother might prioritize mercy. Similarly, an \"evil\" character could be a\nruthless tyrant or a cunning manipulator. The alignment system helps\nplayers think about their characters\' motivations and can guide\ndecision-making within the game, but it\'s always up to individual\ninterpretation.\n\nGood and evil characters receive bonus experience for\nslaying a character of the opposite alignment.',0,'2023-08-19 20:02:51','Giaken'),(1100245,'ethos orderly neutral chaotic','Lawful (often referred to as Orderly): Characters with a lawful alignment\nbelieve in a structured society, rules, order, and tradition. They value\ndiscipline, responsibility, and adherence to a set code of behavior,\nwhether personal or dictated by a governing body. Lawful characters might\nrespect authority, keep their promises, and try to always act within the\nconfines of the law. Their predictability is both a strength and a\nweakness. It\'s important to note that \"lawful\" doesn\'t necessarily mean\n\"good\"; a character can be lawful and evil, adhering strictly to a code or\nset of laws that are oppressive or harmful. \n\nNeutral (with respect to ethos): Neutral characters, in terms of ethos, fall \nbetween the extremes of lawfulness and chaos. They might respect order and \nauthority when it suits them or their goals but don\'t inherently adhere to \nthem. Similarly, they don\'t actively seek to disrupt order or sow chaos. \nTheir actions are often driven by what seems appropriate at the moment, \nmaking them flexible and pragmatic. They tend to prioritize personal \nfreedom and will generally go with whatever system or approach offers \nthem the best balance of security and freedom. \n\nChaotic: Chaotic characters value individual freedom over\nstructure and order. They are skeptical of authority and often resist\nrules, regulations, and traditions, seeing them as constraints. They\nprioritize personal freedom and often act based on their whims or personal\ndesires rather than any external code of behavior. Like with the lawful\nalignment, \"chaotic\" does not inherently mean \"evil\"; a chaotic good\ncharacter, for example, might defy oppressive laws to do what they believe\nis right.',0,'2023-08-19 20:09:19','Giaken'),(1100250,'OLC create edit dig saveworld worldsave','Commands are:\nCreate\ncreate area [name] [vnumstart] [vnumend]\n		create room [vnum]\n		create npc [vnum]\n		create item [vnum]\n			Or: create reset [vnum] [desintation] [count] [maxcount]\n\nEdit\nedit area [name]\n\nedit room [vnum]\nedit room [name|description|sector|exits] {{value}\n\nsectors are inside, city, forest, field, hills, mountain, swamp, \ndesert, cave, underground, waterswim, waternoswim, river, ocean, air, road, underwater\n\nEdit room exits {{direction} [keywords, description, destination, flags, size, keys, delete] {{arguments}\n\nedit npc [vnum]\nedit npc [name|description|level|gold|longdescription|shortdescription|flags|\ndamagedice|guild|protects|hitpointdice|manapointdice|affectedby] {{value}\n\nflags are Practice NoAlign ColorOn SkipAutoDeletePrompt AutoAssist AutoExit AutoLoot AutoSac \n	AutoGold AutoSplit Evaluation Betrayer HeroImm HolyLight CanLoot NoSummon NoFollow NoTransfer \n	PlayerDenied Frozen AssistPlayer AssistAll AssistVnum AssistAlign AssistRace Sentinel Scavenger \n	CabalMob Aggressive Stay_Area Stay_Area Wimpy Pet Trainer Trainer Trainer NoTrack Undead \n	Cleric Mage Thief Warrior NoPurge Outdoors Indoors IsHealer Banker Brief NPC Changer Healer \n	Shopkeeper Area_Attack\n\naffectflags are Blind, Invisible, DetectEvil, DetectEvil, DetectInvis, DetectInvis, DetectMagic, \nDetectMagic, Detect_Hidden, Detect_Hidden, Detect_Good, Detect_Good, DetectIllusion, DetectIllusion, \nSanctuary, Faerie_Fire, Infrared, Curse, Poison, Protect_Evil, ProtectionGood, Sneak, Hide, Sleep, \nCharm, Flying, PassDoor, Haste, Calm, Plague, Weaken, DarkVision, Berserk, Swim, Regeneration, Slow, \nCamouflage\n\nedit item [vnum]\nEdit Item [vnum] [name|description|level|extraflags|wearflags|itemtypes|value|\nnutrition|maxcharges|liquid|material|affects] {{value}\n\nextra flags are Glow Hum Dark Lock Locked Evil Invisibility Invisibility Magic NoDrop \nBless AntiGood AntiNeutral AntiEvil NoRemove NoPurge RotDeath VisDeath Fixed NoDisarm \nNoLocate MeltDrop Closable Closeable PickProof Closed WeaponFlaming Poison Heart \nPouchNourishment EverfullSkin BurnProof Flaming Frost Vorpal Shocking Unholy Sharp \nTwoHands NoUncurse SellExtract PutIn PutOn PutAt StandAt StandOn SitAt SitIn SitOn \nRestIn RestOn RestAt SleepAt SleepOn SleepIn Inventory Outfit\n\nwear flags are Take Finger About Neck Head Legs Feet Hands Wield Hold WearFloat WearFloat \nTattoo Body Waist Wrist Arms Shield NoSac\n*** Take is required to pick up an item\n\nitemtypes are Silver Gold Light Scroll Wand Staff Weapon Treasure Armor Potion Clothing \nFurniture Trash Container DrinkContainer Key Food Money Boat NPCCorpse Corpse \nFountain Pill Map Portal RoomKey Gem Jewelry Cabal Instrument Skeleton\n\nDig\ndig [direction] [vnum] {{flags}\nflags are: door closed locked window pickproof nopass nobash hidden\n\nNextVnum\ndisplays the next vnum to use for rooms, npcs or items in an area\n\nWorldsave or Saveworld will save modified areas',52,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100255,'prompt','Syntax: prompt\nSyntax: prompt default\nSyntax: prompt all\n	same as `prompt default`\nSyntax: prompt <%*>\n \nPROMPT with out an argument will turn your prompt on or off.\n \nPROMPT ALL will give you the standard \"<hits mana moves>\" prompt.\n \nPROMPT <%*> where the %* are the various variables you may set yourself.\n        %1 :  Display % of hitpoints\n        %2 :  Display % of mana\n        %3 :  Display % of movement\n        %h :  Display your current hits\n        %H :  Display your maximum hits\n        %m :  Display your current mana\n        %M :  Display your maximum mana\n        %v :  Display your current moves\n        %V :  Display your maximum moves\n        %x :  Display your current experience\n        %X :  Display experience to level\n        %g :  Display your gold held\n        %s :  Display silver carried\n        %a :  Display your alignment\n        %r :  Display the room name you are in\n        %e :  Display the exits from the room in NESWDU style\n        %c :  Display a carriage return (useful for multi-line prompts)\n        %R :  Display the vnum you are in (IMMORTAL ONLY)\n        %z :  Display the area name you are in (IMMORTAL ONLY)\n \nExample: PROMPT <%hhp %mm %vmv>\nWill set your prompt to \"<10hp 100m 100mv>\"',1,'2023-08-07 14:19:44',''),(1100265,'north','Walk north.',0,'2024-10-11 11:06:37','Giaken'),(1100275,'east','Walk east.',0,'2024-10-11 11:06:37','Giaken'),(1100285,'south','Walk south.',0,'2024-10-11 11:06:37','Giaken'),(1100295,'west','Walk west.',0,'2024-10-11 11:06:37','Giaken'),(1100305,'up','Walk up.',0,'2024-10-11 11:06:37','Giaken'),(1100315,'down','Walk down.',0,'2024-10-11 11:06:37','Giaken'),(1100325,'say','Say something to others in your room.',0,'2024-10-11 11:06:37','Giaken'),(1100335,'sayto','Say something to the person in your room.',0,'2024-10-11 11:06:37','Giaken'),(1100345,'save','Save character information.',0,'2024-10-11 11:06:37','Giaken'),(1100355,'sing','Sing a song.',0,'2024-10-11 11:06:37','Giaken'),(1100365,'reply','Reply to a tell.',0,'2024-10-11 11:06:37','Giaken'),(1100375,'whisper','Whisper something to others in your room.',0,'2024-10-11 11:06:37','Giaken'),(1100385,'whisperto','Whisper something to the person in your room.',0,'2024-10-11 11:06:37','Giaken'),(1100395,'tell','Tell something to a person.',0,'2024-10-11 11:06:37','Giaken'),(1100405,'yell','Yell loudly in the area.',0,'2024-10-11 11:06:37','Giaken'),(1100415,'pray'